WEBVTT

00:08.508 --> 00:12.012
<i>Four Kildare teens who went missing
nearly six weeks ago</i>

00:12.012 --> 00:16.641
<i>are now reported alive, safe,
and back on Kildare Island.</i>

00:16.641 --> 00:19.185
<i>Now a live update
from the sheriff's department.</i>

00:19.185 --> 00:22.814
<i>Yeah, after six weeks,
the four teens that had been missing</i>

00:22.814 --> 00:26.693
<i>from Kildare County have returned,
been reunited with their families.</i>

00:27.318 --> 00:29.779
<i>We're still waiting for details
about their journey,</i>

00:29.779 --> 00:32.615
<i>but I'm sure
they have quite a tale to tell.</i>

00:32.615 --> 00:35.535
<i>We also got word
that the father of one of the teens,</i>

00:35.535 --> 00:38.455
<i>John B Routledge,
who's been presumed dead for a year now</i>,

00:38.455 --> 00:40.582
<i>has also returned alive and well.</i>

00:40.582 --> 00:41.958
<i>Wonders never cease.</i>

00:43.084 --> 00:45.920
<i>Right now,
we're just trying to get those kids</i>

00:45.920 --> 00:48.048
<i>settled back into school,
with their families.</i>

00:48.048 --> 00:49.841
<i>They've been through a lot.</i>

00:53.011 --> 00:54.971
<i>The teens were down
in the Caribbean</i>

00:54.971 --> 00:57.265
<i>with another Kildare teen, Sarah Cameron,</i>

00:57.265 --> 01:00.185
<i>the daughter
of disgraced real estate magnate,</i>

01:00.185 --> 01:03.271
<i>Ward Cameron, who confessed
to the murder of Sheriff Peterkin</i>

01:03.271 --> 01:04.731
<i>two months ago.</i>

01:04.731 --> 01:08.026
<i>All the teens back,
safe and sound on Kildare Island,</i>

01:08.026 --> 01:10.361
<i>and John Routledge back from the dead.</i>

01:10.361 --> 01:13.114
<i>That's about as good
as a result as we could hope for.</i>

01:13.114 --> 01:16.326
When I went back to Tannyhill,
Rafe was on the phone with Ward,

01:16.326 --> 01:19.329
and he just kept saying,
"My thing, this is my thing."

01:19.329 --> 01:21.831
- He had to be talking about the cross.
- Absolutely.

01:21.831 --> 01:25.293
And he's coming
into Wilmington tonight at eight o'clock.

01:26.419 --> 01:28.421
It's being shipped by train
to Raleigh from there,

01:28.421 --> 01:30.340
but this is our chance to get it back.

01:31.174 --> 01:34.511
- You get any other information?
- Uh, Sarah got the cargo number.

01:34.511 --> 01:37.013
-  Okay, well, that's a start.
-  Yeah.

01:37.013 --> 01:39.224
They're definitely fencing
that shit off as we speak.

01:39.224 --> 01:42.060
- So we should probably get a move on.
- Sarah, you hear from John B?

01:42.060 --> 01:44.854
No, I mean, he's probably
off somewhere with his dad.

01:44.854 --> 01:47.816
- But the problem is they have the Twinkie.
- Our transportation.

01:49.025 --> 01:49.901
Um...

01:49.901 --> 01:52.320
- I could ask Heyward for the truck.
- Uh, what?

01:52.320 --> 01:56.074
- Yeah, that's gonna go well.
- I know, but we have no other options.

01:56.658 --> 01:57.909
Absolutely not!

01:57.909 --> 02:00.328
This might be our last opportunity
to go get that cross.

02:00.328 --> 02:02.288
- Is that so?

02:02.872 --> 02:05.250
- I could just get to the mainland--
- Oh boy.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.793
Pop, please! Come on!

02:06.793 --> 02:09.629
This is about our heritage, our family.

02:09.629 --> 02:11.089
This is our thing.

02:11.089 --> 02:14.551
You wanna know what our thing is?
Doing what we say we're gonna do.

02:14.551 --> 02:17.846
Keeping our promises.
Exceeding expectations.

02:17.846 --> 02:19.931
You used to understand that!

02:19.931 --> 02:21.391
Just...

02:21.975 --> 02:24.269
And I still do! I still understand that.

02:24.269 --> 02:26.437
But, Pop, please,
this is the last opportunity,

02:26.437 --> 02:30.275
and I won't ask you for anything else,
and I promise you, I'm done, I swear.

02:30.275 --> 02:33.069
- Please, please let me do this. Mama.
- Uh-uh.

02:33.778 --> 02:36.573
- You on board with this?
- Gotta strike while the iron's hot.

02:36.573 --> 02:37.949
Get off my counter!

02:38.908 --> 02:40.910
Pop, I know appearances
are against me right now,

02:40.910 --> 02:43.621
but please, I will do anything I have to.
I'll work triple shifts.

02:43.621 --> 02:44.998
I'll never leave the house again.

02:44.998 --> 02:47.667
Just please let me go
to Wilmington with your truck.

02:53.882 --> 02:54.966
Get out of here.

02:54.966 --> 02:58.887
Before your mama talk some sense into me,
but you can't take my truck.

02:59.929 --> 03:02.682
- Pop, we're going to need transportation.
- That is not my problem.

03:02.682 --> 03:06.227
I got deliveries.
Somebody's got to keep the lights on.

03:06.811 --> 03:10.064
You know?
Just in case you don't make it big.

03:10.064 --> 03:11.816
All right. Thank you so much.

03:11.816 --> 03:13.193
- Yeah.
- I won't let you down.

03:13.193 --> 03:15.570
- Appreciate you, Pop.
- Don't break any laws.

03:16.070 --> 03:18.698
- Try to keep him out of trouble!
- I'll try!

03:18.698 --> 03:21.451
<i>- ♪ I know a man, he's a powerful man ♪</i>

03:21.451 --> 03:24.370
<i>♪ Got the people in his power
In the palm of his hand ♪</i>

03:28.958 --> 03:30.668
<i>- ♪ He started at the bottom-- ♪
-</i>

03:30.668 --> 03:33.213
- Here we are. Gunning for the big prize.

03:33.213 --> 03:36.716
See, the idol,
it has the directions to El Dorado on it.

03:36.716 --> 03:38.718
The diary should lead us
to the other half,

03:38.718 --> 03:40.386
which is why Singh wants it so badly.

03:40.386 --> 03:41.971
But we got the jump on him this time.

03:41.971 --> 03:45.850
If we put the whole thing together,
both halves, and decipher it,

03:47.185 --> 03:49.187
mountain of gold, here we come.

03:50.313 --> 03:52.982
- Let's go find this church.
- Mountain of gold, huh?

03:54.317 --> 03:56.903
So we're looking for 17 Society Street.

03:57.528 --> 04:00.698
Uh, it should be
an old church with a graveyard.

04:02.867 --> 04:04.661
- Uh, 17, you said?
-  Catholic church...

04:04.661 --> 04:07.163
- Seventeen Society Street. That's it.
- Seventeen.

04:07.163 --> 04:09.457
- No, no, no, no.

04:09.457 --> 04:11.292
- This can't be right.
- Right, right.

04:11.292 --> 04:14.462
Because we've been right so many times.
Why would we be wrong now, Dad?

04:14.462 --> 04:16.881
Don't get smart with me.
I don't need that right now, boy.

04:16.881 --> 04:18.841
This doesn't make any sense.

04:18.841 --> 04:22.470
This should be a church and a graveyard,
not a damn Thai restaurant.

04:23.554 --> 04:25.974
Maybe it's numbered wrong. It can't be.

04:27.308 --> 04:29.435
Hey, great explorer?

04:30.770 --> 04:31.854
Check it out.

04:32.438 --> 04:35.191
"Stood until
the Great Earthquake of 1886."

04:35.191 --> 04:36.776
Charleston Museum?

04:38.653 --> 04:41.990
Well, I'll be damned.
You are good for something, son.

04:42.657 --> 04:44.659
Charleston Museum, eh?

04:45.535 --> 04:46.536
Plan B.

04:49.163 --> 04:51.457
Honey, I am listening to you.
I'm just having a hard time.

04:51.457 --> 04:54.085
So I need you
to walk me through it one more time.

04:54.085 --> 04:57.463
- The Cross of Santo Domingo that we found.
- Right.

04:57.463 --> 04:59.132
We thought it was gone forever.

04:59.132 --> 05:02.552
We just find out
it's... it's gonna be in Wilmington tonight.

05:02.552 --> 05:06.264
- Okay. And the cross is Pope's family--
- Pope's family heirloom.

05:06.264 --> 05:08.641
- Okay.
- Priceless historical artifact.

05:08.641 --> 05:11.060
Priceless,
which you're telling me that you found?

05:11.060 --> 05:13.771
We found it,
and then Rafe and Ward stole it from us.

05:13.771 --> 05:16.482
- Wait, do you know how insane you sound?
- Baby.

05:16.482 --> 05:17.734
- Ward is dead.
- He's not dead.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.652
We've been over this part a million times!

05:19.652 --> 05:21.904
You understand that
this is hard to follow, right?

05:21.904 --> 05:23.489
I mean, we had a funeral for the man.

05:23.489 --> 05:25.366
I get how it sounds, but he's alive.

05:25.366 --> 05:28.286
I wish he wasn't, but he is.
Why would I lie?

05:28.286 --> 05:29.412
He's alive.

05:30.913 --> 05:32.081
- JJ?
- Yeah?

05:33.082 --> 05:34.292
A little help?

05:36.252 --> 05:38.463
- Ward's alive in the Caribbean.
-  Yes.

05:39.005 --> 05:42.133
He's living off the loot
that he stole from us, and, uh,

05:42.133 --> 05:44.218
yeah, he's flying across to Wilmington.

05:44.218 --> 05:45.595
Give me a break, man.

05:45.595 --> 05:48.431
You're right. What do I know, though?
Just saw with my own two eyes.

05:48.431 --> 05:51.476
- So did Kiara, but whatever.
- I'm skeptical, okay?

05:51.476 --> 05:54.604
I am skeptical, JJ,
as in "I think it's all bullshit."

05:54.604 --> 05:56.522
I think you've been led astray, Kiara.

05:56.522 --> 05:57.690
- And you, JJ--
- Mike.

05:57.690 --> 06:00.193
- Let's get this out in the open.
- Can we take it down a little?

06:00.193 --> 06:03.988
Let me tell you something.
You need to understand that I do get it.

06:04.489 --> 06:07.075
- Sure, you do. Yeah. Sure. Sure do.
-  Do you hear me? I do.

06:07.075 --> 06:09.535
I like you, JJ, and I bet
you're fricking fun to hang with,

06:09.535 --> 06:14.832
ditch school with, go down to the break,
because I was once just like you, bro.

06:14.832 --> 06:16.667
I didn't think that anything mattered.

06:16.667 --> 06:20.338
Thought I could make up any bullshit story
and these stupid Kooks would believe it.

06:20.338 --> 06:21.255
Mom.

06:22.256 --> 06:24.425
But then I learned about hard work

06:24.425 --> 06:26.344
and about what really mattered.

06:26.344 --> 06:30.515
All I care about,
<i>all</i> that I care about is my daughter.

06:31.391 --> 06:32.350
That's it.

06:33.643 --> 06:36.729
And all that I know is
that she was a lot better off

06:37.355 --> 06:38.898
before she met you and your friends.

06:38.898 --> 06:41.692
-  Dad, I was never better off!
-  Yes, you were.

06:41.692 --> 06:43.111
- Please.
- I was miserable.

06:43.111 --> 06:45.947
- Miserable? No, no.
-  Take it down a notch. Listen.

06:45.947 --> 06:50.034
No, these Pogues
have ruined my daughter's life.

06:50.743 --> 06:53.121
Didn't mean any disrespect, Mr. Carrera.

06:55.748 --> 06:57.500
- Y'all have a good day.
- Yeah.

06:58.292 --> 06:59.335
Lovely home.

06:59.335 --> 07:02.130
- What are you doing?
- What am I doing? Protecting my daughter.

07:02.130 --> 07:03.506
- Can we please--
- Wait a second.

07:03.506 --> 07:06.384
Everybody says it,
that he's a liar and a thief.

07:06.384 --> 07:08.428
- He's just like his father.
-  Don't go there.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.471
Please don't bring him into this.

07:10.471 --> 07:13.141
-  Don't bring him into this?
-  He's nothing like his dad.

07:13.141 --> 07:15.977
- Nothing like his dad. You don't know him.
-  I don't him?

07:15.977 --> 07:18.813
-  They're nothing alike.
-  I know you. Where are you going?

07:18.813 --> 07:21.274
I listened to you guys.
Y'all can listen to me.

07:21.274 --> 07:23.568
This isn't fair. No, I listened to you.

07:23.568 --> 07:25.778
- This isn't fair?
- Y'all were supposed to listen to me.

07:25.778 --> 07:28.781
Please just wait. Please wait.
Just wait one second, please.

07:28.781 --> 07:30.992
I promised myself
if I had a second chance,

07:30.992 --> 07:33.327
I'd try and be different,
and I'm trying to be different.

07:33.327 --> 07:34.745
Okay, I got to go.

07:36.414 --> 07:37.665
I want you take this.

07:38.624 --> 07:40.418
There's a credit card on the back.

07:40.418 --> 07:42.044
If you get into trouble,

07:43.087 --> 07:45.089
if you need help, you call me.

07:46.299 --> 07:47.300
I will.

07:47.967 --> 07:49.218
I will, Mom.

07:49.218 --> 07:51.804
- I love you. I gotta go. I'll be back.
- Okay.

07:51.804 --> 07:54.265
- I love you. Please be careful.
- I'll be back.

07:55.266 --> 07:56.767
Jayj.

07:56.767 --> 07:57.768
I'm sorry.

08:00.396 --> 08:01.314
Jayj, wait.

08:02.773 --> 08:05.443
- My dad's literally the worst.
- It's whatever.

08:05.443 --> 08:07.403
I already know what they think of me.

08:09.697 --> 08:11.282
They think the same about me.

08:11.866 --> 08:12.825
You ready?

08:15.453 --> 08:16.871
- Yeah.

08:16.871 --> 08:19.332
<i>♪ I overheard that she was 19 ♪</i>

08:19.332 --> 08:22.460
<i>♪ She's got a fake ID and a nose ring ♪</i>

08:22.460 --> 08:25.421
<i>♪ Those kind of girls tend
To know things ♪</i>

08:25.421 --> 08:27.507
<i>♪ Better than I do... ♪</i>

08:35.973 --> 08:37.099
All right.

08:38.809 --> 08:40.937
Just follow my lead. Okay, kid?

08:41.562 --> 08:42.563
Hey, sharpen up.

08:47.235 --> 08:48.778
Hello, sir.

08:48.778 --> 08:51.739
I wonder if I could have
a word with your chief of collections.

08:51.739 --> 08:54.659
Dr. Pierce is
out doing fieldwork till June.

08:54.659 --> 08:57.161
- Can I help you with something?
- Well, hopefully.

08:57.662 --> 08:59.997
I'm Dr. Marion from up at USC.

08:59.997 --> 09:01.624
Paleogenetics mostly.

09:01.624 --> 09:05.002
Anyway, I'm interested in seeing
some items you have in your collection.

09:05.002 --> 09:08.381
Specifically pieces retrieved
from the excavation at Trinity Church

09:08.381 --> 09:09.757
back in the 1880s.

09:09.757 --> 09:13.302
You could submit a written request
to get access to the archives.

09:13.302 --> 09:15.179
I was really hoping
to poke around there today.

09:15.179 --> 09:16.931
I got one of my students with me.

09:16.931 --> 09:20.977
They don't let folks down there
after that Egyptologist weaseled in

09:20.977 --> 09:23.771
and proved a bunch
of the Pharaoh collection were fakes.

09:23.771 --> 09:25.398
- I remember that.

09:25.398 --> 09:27.692
You'll have to go through the protocols.

09:27.692 --> 09:31.821
Well, where.... where are the archives?
Are they... are they here on-site?

09:31.821 --> 09:36.158
No, downtown museum storage,
end of Broad Street, uh, near the Battery.

09:36.158 --> 09:39.161
I'd take you, but they won't give me
one of them key cards.

09:39.161 --> 09:40.955
Above my pay grade.

09:40.955 --> 09:44.125
You got to be a director
like Ms. Flannery here.

09:44.125 --> 09:46.752
- Hello, Ms. Flannery.
-  Good afternoon.

09:47.878 --> 09:49.964
-  Key card, huh?

09:49.964 --> 09:51.048
Understood.

09:51.632 --> 09:54.343
All right.
Well, thank you for the information.

09:54.343 --> 09:56.137
You've been most helpful, okay?

09:56.137 --> 09:57.179
Have a good day.

09:59.890 --> 10:02.977
Honestly, the hardest part
is gonna be security, all right?

10:02.977 --> 10:05.313
So most of the guys
are gonna be at the rail yard.

10:05.313 --> 10:07.148
We'll need to find
some place and guard it,

10:07.148 --> 10:09.692
maybe a little further down the line,
like a whistle-stop.

10:09.692 --> 10:10.610
Yeah.

10:10.610 --> 10:13.070
You guys are getting
ahead of yourselves per usual.

10:13.070 --> 10:15.364
We don't have a way
to transport the cross.

10:15.364 --> 10:17.783
What you think? On JJ's motorcycle?

10:17.783 --> 10:19.410
That's not my fault.

10:19.410 --> 10:20.953
Oh, everyone. All right, all me.

10:20.953 --> 10:22.163
Okay, other options.

10:22.163 --> 10:25.124
I was just, uh, surfing the Soup Bowl.
Oh my goodness.

10:25.124 --> 10:27.418
- Oh my God.
-  Oh my God, what?

10:29.337 --> 10:30.546
Is that Topper?

10:31.047 --> 10:33.257
Why... is he everywhere?

10:33.257 --> 10:34.467
Perfect.

10:34.467 --> 10:35.968
- Hey, Jayj.
- What?

10:35.968 --> 10:38.387
I bet you Topper has
a way to transport the cross.

10:38.387 --> 10:41.015
Actually, Pope's right.
He does have a rig.

10:41.015 --> 10:42.350
- No.
- Yes.

10:42.350 --> 10:44.185
- No. Absolutely not.
-  Yes, come on.

10:44.185 --> 10:46.270
Sarah, you already got him
whipped anyway, all right?

10:46.270 --> 10:48.230
So why don't you just take one
for the team?

10:48.230 --> 10:49.857
What would John B say?

10:49.857 --> 10:51.692
I think John B will completely understand.

10:51.692 --> 10:54.278
Think about the circumstances.
It's about treasure.

10:54.278 --> 10:55.821
We can handle John B.

10:57.073 --> 10:58.407
Just talk to him.

11:00.451 --> 11:02.328
So this is your master plan, huh?

11:02.328 --> 11:03.412
Rob an old lady?

11:03.412 --> 11:05.039
Not... rob.

11:05.915 --> 11:07.333
Appropriate, all right?

11:07.875 --> 11:10.169
Temporarily acquire an object
that has no value for her

11:10.169 --> 11:11.545
and is essential for us.

11:12.046 --> 11:13.547
Okay, I just wanna...

11:13.547 --> 11:14.924
Hey, there she is.

11:15.633 --> 11:17.009
It's game time, kid.

11:17.802 --> 11:19.887
- No. What are you doing?

11:19.887 --> 11:21.389
Do you know where we are?

11:21.889 --> 11:23.849
We are on the hot damn Hillary Step,
okay, boy?

11:23.849 --> 11:25.309
One beat away from the mountaintop.

11:25.309 --> 11:28.396
We can't let a little thing
like federal armed robbery get in the way.

11:28.396 --> 11:31.315
- I taught you how to shoplift.
- Are you seriously bringing that up now?

11:31.315 --> 11:33.359
But that came in handy
when I was gone, didn't it?

11:33.359 --> 11:34.694
Oh Jesus. Come on, man.

11:34.694 --> 11:38.280
So here's another little lesson.
A little baby step.

11:42.243 --> 11:45.913
J-bird, hey, you gotta
let that thing go out there at sea, kid.

11:45.913 --> 11:47.415
Lighten up a little.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.500
It was us or them.

11:50.918 --> 11:52.378
What did you want me to do?

11:52.878 --> 11:56.090
And right now,
we got another thing that needs doing.

11:58.718 --> 12:01.679
- I think it's better if you do it.
- Oh, me. You want me to go, your son?

12:01.679 --> 12:03.597
- To go hold up that old lady?
- That's right.

12:03.597 --> 12:07.268
I assure you, once we get to Orinoco,
it will get harder.

12:07.268 --> 12:08.185
Look.

12:08.936 --> 12:11.313
- Hey, see? It's empty.
- Yeah, yeah. I get it. I get it.

12:11.313 --> 12:14.775
You trust me now?
Now I need to know that I can trust you.

12:14.775 --> 12:15.818
Okay?

12:15.818 --> 12:18.154
And don't ask
for her key card specifically.

12:18.654 --> 12:20.197
All right? Get her whole wallet.

12:20.197 --> 12:22.074
We don't want anybody to know
what we're after.

12:22.074 --> 12:23.909
She's leaving now.
This is our only chance.

12:23.909 --> 12:26.871
Go on. It's game time, son.
Go! Get that bag, boy.

12:27.705 --> 12:28.831
That's it.

12:36.464 --> 12:38.340
- Ma'am.
- Ooh goodness.

12:38.340 --> 12:41.135
- You snuck up on me.
- Yeah, sorry about that.

12:41.886 --> 12:43.679
Can I help you with something?

12:44.764 --> 12:45.639
Come on.

12:48.142 --> 12:51.187
- Look, I was just wondering, uh--
-  Wondering what, son?

12:54.607 --> 12:56.025
What are you doing?

12:56.025 --> 12:58.652
I just need your bag, please.

12:59.945 --> 13:02.490
You're not getting my bag, son.

13:02.490 --> 13:04.533
I will bring it back
with everything inside of it.

13:04.533 --> 13:06.160
- Can I please just have your bag?
- Shit.

13:07.536 --> 13:10.331
You're about
the most pitiful excuse for a thief

13:10.331 --> 13:12.041
I've ever seen in my life.

13:12.958 --> 13:16.045
What's the matter with you?
Does your mama know where you are?

13:16.045 --> 13:17.963
You need to be ashamed of yourself.

13:31.477 --> 13:33.813
Ain't exactly Jesse James, are you, kid?

13:34.939 --> 13:35.940
Come on.

13:37.149 --> 13:39.944
We'll just get into the archives
the old-fashioned way.

13:42.154 --> 13:46.408
I just can't believe you're here.
I saw the news. I... I texted you.

13:46.408 --> 13:49.203
I didn't even know
if you were alive, Sarah.

13:49.203 --> 13:50.162
How are you?

