- How you gonna do that?

17:53.655 --> 17:55.365
I got an uncle up in New Bern, right?

17:55.365 --> 17:57.618
When he got tipsy,
he'd just throw an old chain

17:57.618 --> 18:00.037
across the tracks,
just for shits and giggles.

18:00.037 --> 18:04.792
And that old little chain
would stop all the train traffic

18:05.459 --> 18:06.919
in coastal Carolina.

18:06.919 --> 18:08.796
- A chain?
-  He's actually right.

18:08.796 --> 18:12.049
There's a low-voltage current
that runs across all rail tracks.

18:12.049 --> 18:13.884
Throw a chain on it,
you close that circuit.

18:13.884 --> 18:16.929
It would read as another train.
Crossing lights come down.

18:17.429 --> 18:20.808
- Science is actually pretty sound.
- Science. I knew my science.

18:21.433 --> 18:22.976
Well, we don't have a chain.

18:23.894 --> 18:28.232
No, but I bet Topper's dad
has jumper cables in the truck.

18:29.024 --> 18:30.484
- Would that work?
- Yeah.

18:30.484 --> 18:32.319
What's going on?
Are we doing this?

18:34.029 --> 18:36.156
All right, you all wait here.

18:36.156 --> 18:38.992
Me and Pope will go look for it
and send a signal once we find it.

18:38.992 --> 18:41.078
- Do we actually have a plan right now?
- Think we do.

18:41.078 --> 18:43.580
- That's impressive.
- Let's not jinx it. Come on.

18:43.580 --> 18:45.415
-  Nobody ever listens to me.

18:45.415 --> 18:47.918
-  Try this.
-  I don't think it's gonna work.

18:47.918 --> 18:51.755
- I have shoulders. I do, I do.
-  You do. Lovely shoulders.

18:51.755 --> 18:54.675
- No, this'll be good with that.
-  Oh. Oh, great.

18:54.675 --> 18:56.009
Shh.

19:00.514 --> 19:02.808
Hey! Look, upstairs.

19:06.979 --> 19:08.897
-  You're trouble!
- Shh!

19:10.691 --> 19:12.860
Look at this place.

19:13.986 --> 19:15.112
It's a gold mine.

19:15.696 --> 19:18.991
Check everything, just check everything
Look for anything Trinity Church.

19:18.991 --> 19:22.536
Anything late 1800s.
Habitats, biodiversity.

19:23.120 --> 19:26.957
Antiques. Pretty cool stuff
but not what we're looking for.

19:26.957 --> 19:29.251
Tiles, grass dividers, come on.

19:31.670 --> 19:35.382
Underground Railroad, rocks.
What we got? Uniforms, coats, buttons?

19:35.883 --> 19:38.010
Swords, scabbards.

19:40.846 --> 19:43.265
Some porcelain, silver plates.

19:43.807 --> 19:44.933
Pottery.

19:46.643 --> 19:47.644
Religious.

19:51.523 --> 19:53.317
John B, hey.

19:54.234 --> 19:55.402
The Trinity Church.

19:57.696 --> 19:59.781
- This is it, buddy.
- No way.

19:59.781 --> 20:01.325
Okay.

20:01.992 --> 20:04.119
Look at this. Look at this, boy.

20:05.704 --> 20:08.123
The mother lode.

20:10.334 --> 20:13.879
This could be it, Bird.
Five hundred years in the making.

20:15.214 --> 20:16.548
Here we are.

20:22.387 --> 20:23.680
It's this track here.

20:25.265 --> 20:27.559
Remember, it's car 750X.

20:27.559 --> 20:30.229
All right, 2-0-4-5.

20:33.232 --> 20:34.858
2-0-1-7.

20:37.819 --> 20:40.572
