23:11.306 --> 23:12.641
Near misses.

23:12.641 --> 23:16.395
-  Hey, Dad, we missed one.

23:18.105 --> 23:20.315
Uh, Dad, we actually missed a box.

23:20.315 --> 23:22.442
-  What is this?

23:23.276 --> 23:25.237
-  What?
- Some sort of rock?

23:33.370 --> 23:34.996
- Look.
- What's it labeled?

23:34.996 --> 23:37.457
"Trinity Church, miscellaneous."

23:41.420 --> 23:42.421
Um...

23:42.963 --> 23:43.797
Dad?

23:44.756 --> 23:46.049
This... this...

23:47.300 --> 23:49.219
This is... this is Kalinago.

23:51.304 --> 23:53.265
A vanished Indigenous people.

23:59.229 --> 24:00.063
Dad?

24:00.647 --> 24:02.524
This could be it, John B.
This could be it.

24:03.191 --> 24:05.569
Look, look.
The stones, they're the same color.

24:05.569 --> 24:08.321
- Holy shit.

24:08.321 --> 24:10.449
-  Let's see if it fits.
- Oh my...

24:11.158 --> 24:12.826
Look, look.

24:15.245 --> 24:16.705
Dude, Dad!

24:23.462 --> 24:24.588
Dad. Dad.

24:25.422 --> 24:28.717
Look at this.
This is the cat serpent.

24:31.261 --> 24:33.054
I think this is a skylight.

24:40.061 --> 24:41.396
Oh, Birdy Boy.

24:43.607 --> 24:44.983
All right.

24:50.405 --> 24:53.283
What the shit is that?

24:53.283 --> 24:56.328
Look at that, boy.
Look at that.

24:56.328 --> 24:59.664
We did it, son.

25:00.874 --> 25:01.833
Together.

25:02.584 --> 25:06.087
Just like I said we would.
You see that? You found it, boy.

25:06.087 --> 25:08.089
What--

25:09.132 --> 25:12.093
We did it.
We did it. That a boy.

25:25.649 --> 25:26.816
Hey!

25:26.816 --> 25:27.859
What?

25:28.443 --> 25:29.736
Just so you know,

25:30.362 --> 25:32.614
I'm not normally this crazy.

25:32.614 --> 25:36.701
It's just getting this cross back.
It means a lot to me.

25:36.701 --> 25:38.745
I have to do this.

25:38.745 --> 25:42.249
- It's worth it.
- It better be after all this shit, man.

25:46.419 --> 25:48.505
- This should be far enough.
- All right.

25:51.216 --> 25:52.759
- You good?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

25:52.759 --> 25:55.178
All right? Oh God, you can hear it coming.

25:55.178 --> 25:57.556
- Let's fry this sucker.
-  All right.

25:57.556 --> 25:59.975
Okay, now, all you have to do...

25:59.975 --> 26:00.976
Do your trick.

26:00.976 --> 26:02.727
...is change the current.

26:02.727 --> 26:04.688
- Let's go.
- Don't get electrocuted, please.

26:04.688 --> 26:06.982
Yeah, no promises with that.
Three, two, one.

26:06.982 --> 26:08.608
- And red.

26:08.608 --> 26:09.734
Moment of truth.

26:13.029 --> 26:15.115
Come on, man. Come on. Come on.

26:17.576 --> 26:19.744
Okay. That's what he would do.
That's literally what my--

26:19.744 --> 26:21.621
So then it'd change red-- Oh my God.

26:22.205 --> 26:24.457
Think, think, think.
Okay, what if I blockaded the track?

26:24.457 --> 26:26.167
That's what I could do. Maybe put a tree?

26:26.167 --> 26:29.546
Uh, hey. The train touches
both sides of the track.

26:36.136 --> 26:38.096
Come on. Come on.

26:41.808 --> 26:43.893
Please, we don't have a plan B

26:45.020 --> 26:47.564
- Yes. Yes. Yes.
- That's what I'm talking about!

26:49.065 --> 26:52.027
- You're a genius. I was gonna do that.
- Science. No, it's all you.

26:52.027 --> 26:53.570
And now we wait.

27:02.912 --> 27:05.165
It's gonna work. It's gonna work.

27:09.377 --> 27:12.589
The train's stopping.
It's stopping. They did it.

27:13.590 --> 27:15.216
- Shit.
- Come on.

27:19.512 --> 27:21.848
- She's slowing down.
- We got brakes, dude.

27:24.017 --> 27:27.395
Hey, dispatch. Trackside signal lights
are red at block 247.

27:27.395 --> 27:29.731
Repeat, red at block 247. Standing by.

27:36.321 --> 27:37.906
Go check it out. Will you?

27:37.906 --> 27:41.534
This is it, my boy.
There is blood on the tracks.

27:41.534 --> 27:43.912
- We are hot on the trail.
- Yeah. Feels great.

27:43.912 --> 27:45.997
Ha, you're right about that, boy.
It feels great!

27:45.997 --> 27:46.915
Wait, wait, wait.

27:47.832 --> 27:48.792
Dad.

27:50.502 --> 27:52.420
Dad, where's the car? Dad.

27:52.420 --> 27:54.547
It's-- Somebody must have stole it.

27:54.547 --> 27:56.925
Why would somebody steal the Twinkie?

27:56.925 --> 28:00.178
That's all I've got.
That's all I've got, Dad.

28:00.178 --> 28:03.223
- What?
- Oh boy. Looks like Carla found us.

28:03.807 --> 28:05.350
Great.

28:05.350 --> 28:08.311
- Limbrey stole the Twinkie.
- Come on, I know where she lives.

28:11.898 --> 28:12.982
Shit, man.

28:12.982 --> 28:14.609
I almost broke my arm.

28:15.735 --> 28:17.612
- Can you pick the lock?
- Sure.

28:21.950 --> 28:24.953
-  Kie. Back up. Back up.
- Shh!

28:26.246 --> 28:28.456
- Shit.
- No, no, no. That's not part of the plan.

28:32.919 --> 28:35.088
-  You almost done?
- Almost.

28:35.922 --> 28:37.924
-  Hey! Hey!
- Shit.

28:37.924 --> 28:39.884
-  Stay right here.
- Oh shit.

28:40.969 --> 28:42.721
Hey, what are you doing here?

28:42.721 --> 28:44.764
Sir, I'm so sorry.
It is not what it looks like.

28:44.764 --> 28:46.349
I know it looks like we're criminals,

28:46.349 --> 28:48.184
but that's not our intention.
I promise, sir.

28:49.269 --> 28:50.645
What is going on here?

28:51.312 --> 28:53.690
-  Hell if I know.
-  What is this bullshit?

28:54.482 --> 28:55.483
You see this?

28:57.861 --> 28:59.946
What are you doing here?
It's very dangerous.

28:59.946 --> 29:03.825
Just trying to get to the next town over.
We're running away from home. That's it.

29:03.825 --> 29:06.661
You know, I'm not buying it.
I'm sorry, I'm calling for backup.

29:06.661 --> 29:09.664
Sir, please, I see you're married.
Sir, please.

29:09.664 --> 29:11.458
We're in love.
That's all we're trying to do.

29:11.458 --> 29:14.210
We're just trying to get married,
and we can't do that here.

29:17.213 --> 29:18.339
Unhook that for me.

29:19.549 --> 29:20.842
What is going on?

29:23.595 --> 29:25.221
Please, this is my fiancée.

29:26.848 --> 29:30.268
- Please.
- Our parents won't let us be together but...

29:30.268 --> 29:34.939
Sir, we can't get married in this town,
but I love her so much.

29:34.939 --> 29:37.442
And if you'd just let us
get to the next town,

29:37.442 --> 29:39.319
we're gonna find a priest who'll marry us.

29:39.319 --> 29:41.279
And we just wanna start a life together.

29:41.279 --> 29:43.531
- Throw that in the back for me.
-  All right.

29:49.871 --> 29:50.955
Please.

29:54.167 --> 29:57.921
You guys hopping the rails,
it's illegal, okay? But...

30:01.341 --> 30:03.343
I can't stop what I don't see.

30:04.177 --> 30:07.722
So listen, just... go.

30:07.722 --> 30:09.808
Thank you. Sir, what's your name?

30:09.808 --> 30:11.392
It's Jimmy.

30:11.392 --> 30:13.478
That's gonna be
our first child's name, Jimmy,

30:13.478 --> 30:16.064
because of what you've done today.
Thank you so much.

30:16.773 --> 30:18.191
All right. Go.

30:18.900 --> 30:20.777
-  Thank you.
- I don't wanna see you again.

30:26.074 --> 30:27.742
You're all set over here.

30:27.742 --> 30:30.620
Some asshole
put jumper cables on the tracks.

30:30.620 --> 30:31.913
There you go.

30:33.540 --> 30:34.999
They've had enough time, right?

30:38.419 --> 30:39.629
Got it.

30:39.629 --> 30:41.297
You did it! All right.

30:47.679 --> 30:50.598
