Why do you have this?

32:30.448 --> 32:33.534
If I'm gonna be accused of being a thief,
might as well get something out of it.

32:33.534 --> 32:36.871
- You're just giving them ammunition.
- Ammunition for what, Kie?

32:38.331 --> 32:40.208
They're already against me. So who cares?

32:40.208 --> 32:42.710
They didn't have a reason.
You're giving them a reason.

32:42.710 --> 32:44.712
Know what?
We don't have time for this. Get on.

32:45.546 --> 32:49.008
-  Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
-  Careful, guy! Oh, stop!

32:49.008 --> 32:50.635
Which way you want it to go?

32:50.635 --> 32:53.721
Dispatch, hold up.
We got a train robbery in progress.

32:55.348 --> 32:56.307
Stop!

32:56.307 --> 32:57.392
Hey, stop!

32:57.392 --> 32:59.602
- We gotta go.
-  Hold it right there.

32:59.602 --> 33:00.603
Cops. Come on.

33:00.603 --> 33:02.939
- The cops are coming. Let's go.
- Punch it, Chewie!

33:02.939 --> 33:03.982
Go!

33:03.982 --> 33:06.985
How the hell can you live like this?
You come from a good family.

33:06.985 --> 33:07.944
Just drive!

33:07.944 --> 33:09.612
- Hey, hey, stop!

33:14.867 --> 33:17.370
They took something off the train.
The cops are in pursuit.

33:22.125 --> 33:22.959
Whoa!

33:22.959 --> 33:24.877
Get on the bike, Kie.

33:28.548 --> 33:29.966
That's Top.

33:30.591 --> 33:32.301
And that's the cross. Get on!

33:52.989 --> 33:55.366
- We got somebody on us.
- That's JJ and Kie.

34:05.877 --> 34:07.795
-  J!
- I know. I know.

34:07.795 --> 34:09.380
What the hell is this kid doing?

34:15.636 --> 34:17.221
What is he doing?

34:17.221 --> 34:18.264
I don't know.

34:19.557 --> 34:22.268
- What are you doing?
- Top, keep going straight.

34:22.268 --> 34:24.937
- Y'all be careful. All right?
- Topper, hold it steady.

34:24.937 --> 34:26.272
I'm trying.

34:26.272 --> 34:28.191
- Get ready to jump.
- What?

34:28.191 --> 34:29.233
What?

34:29.233 --> 34:32.612
- Have you lost your mind?
- Probably! Get ready to jump.

34:32.612 --> 34:35.406
Come on. Come on.
I've got you. I've got you. Come on.

34:36.532 --> 34:37.867
Kie, what are you doing?

34:37.867 --> 34:40.995
-  Easy, easy now.

34:40.995 --> 34:42.830
- Be careful.

34:42.830 --> 34:44.999
- Oh sh--

34:44.999 --> 34:45.917
- What?
- Holy sh--

34:47.960 --> 34:49.712
-  You okay?
- Yeah.

34:49.712 --> 34:51.339
Are you good?

34:51.339 --> 34:52.757
Did she make it?

34:58.638 --> 34:59.764
What's he gonna do?

34:59.764 --> 35:02.058
I don't know.
I don't think he knows either.

35:07.271 --> 35:08.689
He's trying to get killed.

35:08.689 --> 35:11.234
Okay, maybe he's just trying
to get rid of the cops.

35:11.234 --> 35:12.318
Let's dance.

35:20.034 --> 35:21.327
Oh, here we go.

35:23.579 --> 35:25.289
- Damn it!

35:29.877 --> 35:31.587
-  He did it! They're chasing him.
- Shit.

35:31.587 --> 35:32.672
Oh God.

35:38.970 --> 35:42.557
- Topper, stop. Stop the truck.
- Oh my God. I'm not stopping the truck.

35:42.557 --> 35:44.725
- Hey! Stop the truck.
- Stop the truck!

35:44.725 --> 35:46.853
- We're going to get JJ.
- Come on, man!

35:46.853 --> 35:51.232
- I'm not going to jail for you. No chance.
- Stop the truck. Please.

35:51.232 --> 35:53.401
All right. All right, damn it!
All right. All right.

35:54.402 --> 35:55.945
Turn around!

35:55.945 --> 35:59.073
- I'm not going... I'm not going to jail.
- Topper, look at me.

35:59.073 --> 36:01.659
They're gonna arrest him.
We can't leave him behind.

36:01.659 --> 36:02.994
Damn it. Damn.

36:27.602 --> 36:30.188
- Go faster. You need to go faster.
-  I'm trying.

36:30.188 --> 36:31.606
- Let's go!
- Move it!

36:31.606 --> 36:34.275
- I'm risking my life for this shit.
-  It's gonna be fine.

36:34.275 --> 36:35.610
- Turn left!
- No, I'm not--

36:35.610 --> 36:38.487
- Go! Yes! Yes! Topper!
- No. I'm getting out of here.

36:42.783 --> 36:44.493
There he is. What is he doing?

36:50.750 --> 36:52.335
- Turn right.
-  Okay!

36:59.926 --> 37:02.261
- No way, he's up on the overpass.

37:07.225 --> 37:09.018
- Oh fuck!

37:17.401 --> 37:19.070
- Pope, go!
-  Go, go!

37:22.531 --> 37:23.950
Jayj.

37:24.492 --> 37:25.576
Jayj!

37:26.285 --> 37:28.162
Jayj? Where is he?

37:28.162 --> 37:29.497
- Shit!
-  No, no, no, no.

37:29.497 --> 37:31.249
JJ? Jayj!

37:31.249 --> 37:33.668
- Ah, man!
-  You all right?

37:33.668 --> 37:34.752
Yeah, I think so.

37:36.921 --> 37:38.589
Where is he?

37:38.589 --> 37:41.050
-  Maybe he's up on the bridge.
- No, no, no.

37:42.468 --> 37:43.803
Sir, you okay?

37:43.803 --> 37:46.597
- Yeah. Just my neck.
- Don't move your neck. Just stay still.

37:51.477 --> 37:54.313
I wish I could say I did that on purpose,

37:54.313 --> 37:58.526
but that was the gnarliest powerslide
I've ever done.

37:59.652 --> 38:01.362
You're alive!

38:01.362 --> 38:03.531
- Dude!
-  I know, I'm surprised too.

38:03.531 --> 38:04.865
Shit, that was gnarly.

38:04.865 --> 38:07.535
That was trucking, dude. Oh Jesus. Oh God.

38:07.535 --> 38:09.745
We really thought
you did it this time, Jayj.

38:09.745 --> 38:11.622
- Hey, did you call the ambulance?
- Yeah.

38:11.622 --> 38:13.624
We got backup coming, sir. Just relax.

38:13.624 --> 38:15.793
The pleasantries are nice,
but we should get out.

38:15.793 --> 38:17.086
Yeah, yeah, let's roll.

38:21.799 --> 38:24.468
Don't... don't ever do that again.

38:28.472 --> 38:31.058
- Hey! Hey, you kids, don't move.
- Go!

38:31.058 --> 38:33.728
Stay right there. I said stay right there!

38:33.728 --> 38:35.271
- We need backup right away.
-  Go!

38:35.271 --> 38:37.148
- Four or five kids in a Dodge Ram.
-  Go!

38:37.148 --> 38:39.483
They're taking off.
They're headed south. Damn it!

38:41.944 --> 38:44.613
So, yeah,
in return for helping me find you,

38:44.613 --> 38:46.824
I told Limbrey I'd get her shroud.

38:46.824 --> 38:48.826
Right, you're talking about
the healing garment,

38:48.826 --> 38:51.329
the one that cures all maladies,
supposedly in the cross.

38:51.329 --> 38:53.372
- Is that what you're referring to?
- That's the one.

38:53.372 --> 38:54.957
It wasn't in the cross. She checked.

38:54.957 --> 38:57.209
That's how I was able to convince her
I had a bead on it.

38:57.209 --> 38:59.837
And do you have a bead
on this magic healing garment?

38:59.837 --> 39:01.922
Currently, I have zero beads.

39:01.922 --> 39:05.134
I don't have a single magic garment
that can heal all maladies.

39:05.134 --> 39:07.428
Oh, and by the way,
that shroud she's after,

39:07.428 --> 39:08.387
it's a known hoax.

39:08.387 --> 39:10.556
Yeah. I could've guessed that.
Do you have a plan?

39:10.556 --> 39:12.016
Sure, always have a plan.

39:12.016 --> 39:15.227
We are gonna prevaricate
our way out of a pickle, son.

39:15.227 --> 39:17.355
- I don't know what that means.
- You'll figure it out.

39:17.355 --> 39:18.731
Play along if you feel like it.

39:18.731 --> 39:20.816
Yeah. I'd play along
if I knew what the word meant.

39:34.246 --> 39:35.289
Hi.

39:35.289 --> 39:36.415
Hi.

39:36.415 --> 39:38.167
Uh, you got my ride, right?

39:38.167 --> 39:42.171
Yeah, I was tracking you,
first on your boat, then on your phone.

39:42.171 --> 39:44.090
I needed to get your attention.

39:44.090 --> 39:46.717
Just checking.
I came down here to see you, of course.

39:46.717 --> 39:47.802
Oh.

39:48.844 --> 39:50.054
Is that so?

39:50.054 --> 39:52.473
That is so... so.

39:54.767 --> 39:56.685
But first, lookee there.

39:57.728 --> 39:59.897
Oh, hey, Ms. Limbrey. What's up?

40:01.899 --> 40:03.109
You found your son.

40:04.485 --> 40:06.362
And you found your father.

40:06.362 --> 40:07.655
How fortunate.

40:08.239 --> 40:09.573
That bond,

40:09.573 --> 40:13.702
so precious, so... fleeting.

40:17.957 --> 40:19.667
Please, come in.

40:20.960 --> 40:22.294
Here, let me help you.

40:25.756 --> 40:26.674
You heard her. Come on.

40:26.674 --> 40:28.384
Can't do this on the front porch?

40:28.384 --> 40:30.302
- Just come on, be cool. Be cool.
- Be cool?

40:30.302 --> 40:31.387
It's okay.

40:33.931 --> 40:38.060
So, as the Spaniards were coming downriver

40:38.561 --> 40:41.313
out of the headwaters, they were attacked.

40:41.897 --> 40:44.442
The Kalinago warriors
began to loot the ship.

40:44.442 --> 40:48.195
And the priest was... was terrified
that the shroud would be taken

40:48.195 --> 40:49.864
if the natives got the cross,

40:50.364 --> 40:53.200
so he... he took it out of the cross. See?

40:53.200 --> 40:56.203
That's why it wasn't there
when you looked. Yeah?

40:56.203 --> 40:57.955
And then that priest

40:57.955 --> 40:59.290
kept the shroud.

40:59.915 --> 41:02.293
And he... he fled. He took cover.

41:03.252 --> 41:04.378
Eventually--

41:04.378 --> 41:08.716
So what my dad is trying to say is that
the priest ended up on the Royal Merchant

41:08.716 --> 41:10.843
'cause he was the sole survivor
of the San Jose fire.

41:10.843 --> 41:11.802
That's right.

41:12.386 --> 41:13.220
Oh.

41:13.220 --> 41:15.723
And we know all this
because of Denmark's diary,

41:15.723 --> 41:17.475
which my son here found.

41:17.475 --> 41:18.684
With a little help.

41:20.060 --> 41:21.854
- Apple doesn't fall far from the tree.
- Yeah.

41:22.438 --> 41:24.023
Then later, the priest,

41:24.607 --> 41:26.400
see, he got dysentery,

41:26.400 --> 41:27.485
and he died.

41:30.279 --> 41:32.364
He was... he was buried here in Charleston.

41:33.991 --> 41:36.243
But if he had the shroud,

41:36.243 --> 41:39.705
why didn't he just... touch it

41:40.706 --> 41:41.874
and heal himself?

41:41.874 --> 41:46.045
That, very valid question. You know,
I was thinking the same thing but--

41:46.045 --> 41:49.798
- That's part of the story.
- Yeah, continue, please.

41:49.798 --> 41:52.801
Because he was so devout,

41:53.886 --> 41:56.847
he was so looking forward

41:57.723 --> 42:00.309
to being reunited
with his Heavenly Father.

42:02.561 --> 42:05.523
We dug up his effects
at the Charleston Museum.

42:09.443 --> 42:10.444
And yes,

42:11.904 --> 42:12.863
we have it.

42:15.991 --> 42:17.451
We have the shroud.

42:21.956 --> 42:24.500
We were just on our way to bring it to you

42:24.500 --> 42:27.670
when you left your... invitation.

42:27.670 --> 42:31.715
I wrapped it up the best I could
with... with what we had on the way.

42:31.715 --> 42:32.883
That is

42:33.926 --> 42:36.387
<i>the</i> shroud right in there.

42:38.055 --> 42:41.016
Thousands of years
to be placed in your hands.

42:45.354 --> 42:48.440
There she is. Behold a thing of magic.

42:51.485 --> 42:54.113
You feel that?

42:56.699 --> 42:58.701
I just got chills. Look at that.

43:01.287 --> 43:02.580
Yes, wow.

43:07.251 --> 43:08.252
That's right.

43:12.089 --> 43:13.924
Do you feel the power of that?

43:52.212 --> 43:55.007
- I'll grab it. I'll just leave it, yeah.
-  You can just--

43:56.425 --> 43:57.509
I don't need your help.

44:17.571 --> 44:18.614
Oh.

44:39.426 --> 44:40.427
I'm healed.

44:43.013 --> 44:43.889
Hallelujah.

44:46.225 --> 44:48.519
Look at you, darling.
How about that?

44:52.648 --> 44:54.900
She walked. It worked.

44:54.900 --> 44:57.236
- What the hell was going on there?

44:57.236 --> 45:00.447
Hey, you have to believe in miracles
if you want them to happen.

45:00.447 --> 45:02.449
It'd be a miracle if this thing starts up.

45:04.159 --> 45:06.829
Gotta believe, boy. I believed it.

45:08.956 --> 45:10.749
El Dorado, here we come.

45:18.298 --> 45:20.968
- Shit, they definitely called it in.
- Top, Top! Turn here!

45:20.968 --> 45:23.220
- Turn here!
- Don't touch... don't touch the driver, man.

45:23.220 --> 45:26.765
- Topper, turn around.
- Stop. He said don't touch the driver!

45:26.765 --> 45:28.767
- It's a liability.
- Then go faster.

45:28.767 --> 45:30.686
If I go faster,
that's gonna draw attention.

45:30.686 --> 45:32.646
Yeah, I feel like that ship has sailed.

45:32.646 --> 45:35.357
You guys are a nightmare.
Do you argue about everything?

45:35.357 --> 45:38.026
- Put the pedal to the metal, boy!
- Yes!

45:38.026 --> 45:40.863
Maybe put it a little bit.
You're going 65!

45:40.863 --> 45:43.907
- All right. Screw it. Here we go.
-  Let's just go faster.

45:43.907 --> 45:46.201
There you go.
That's what I'm talking about.

45:47.369 --> 45:48.620
-  Hey!
-  Stop.

45:51.832 --> 45:53.667
- Stop, stop! We lost the cross!
-  Shit.

45:53.667 --> 45:56.253
- Great, Topper.
- You guys told me to go faster.

46:06.138 --> 46:07.890
-  What the hell?
-  Shit.

46:09.600 --> 46:10.809
It's fake.

46:18.567 --> 46:19.860
It's all a freaking fake.

46:19.860 --> 46:23.697
Of course, we did.
Of course, we stole a fake.

46:25.157 --> 46:26.909
Pope, I'm so sorry.

46:41.548 --> 46:44.676
Y'all hear that? Okay, I can't be here.
My grandfather's a judge.

46:44.676 --> 46:45.803
Dog, would you relax?

46:45.803 --> 46:48.597
They're not gonna think some dude
in flip-flops is a part of a robbery.

46:48.597 --> 46:51.183
Oh yeah, with the crate
sitting right next to my truck.

46:51.183 --> 46:53.393
- I'm sure we'll be fine.
- Pope, we gotta go.

46:53.393 --> 46:55.354
-  Y'all coming?
-  We got to go.

46:55.354 --> 46:56.438
Pope.

46:57.105 --> 46:58.816
Pope, we got to go.

46:58.816 --> 47:00.776
We gonna find it. We gonna find it later.

47:00.776 --> 47:03.612
- Pope, we gotta go.
- We gonna find it. Come on.

47:03.612 --> 47:05.113
Come on. Come on.

47:17.292 --> 47:20.921
This shit is
straight out of the Pope's vault, bro.

47:22.005 --> 47:24.466
You don't think
we can get more for it as it is?

47:24.466 --> 47:26.927
I mean, this straight out of church, bro.

47:36.353 --> 47:38.856
This is how we turn the cross
into untraceable money.

47:43.193 --> 47:44.278
Untraceable, huh?

47:56.582 --> 47:58.959
You know, I heard some crazy shit
that happened last night.

47:58.959 --> 48:00.627
- Is that right?

48:00.627 --> 48:03.463
- You know that fake cross we put in there?
-  Yeah.

48:06.383 --> 48:07.467
It was stolen.

48:08.802 --> 48:11.889
- Does sound like them Pogues, don't it?
- Oh, no doubt.

48:15.392 --> 48:19.229
I mean, I'd pay half the value of this
just to see the look on their faces

48:19.229 --> 48:20.647
when they opened the box.

48:21.899 --> 48:23.108
I'll bet you would.

48:27.279 --> 48:30.365
You know what the melting point
of gold is, Country Club?

48:32.284 --> 48:34.494
1,948 degrees.

48:36.538 --> 48:38.373
Hot enough to melt me and you.

48:38.916 --> 48:42.169
I got to be honest with you, dog.
I don't know if I got this in me, bro.

48:42.169 --> 48:43.128
I do.

48:47.174 --> 48:49.134
Yeah, I knew you did.

48:50.469 --> 48:52.387
It's all yours, Country Club.

49:12.032 --> 49:13.033
There it is.

49:22.876 --> 49:25.170
We're going to hell.
That's for sure.
